    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-05-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-05-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="813"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d813">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.6312 A/6</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Austrian Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Prochnik</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-05-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1928</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 96/R</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to notify Your Excellency
                    that the Federal Government of Austria is willing and ready to conclude with the
                    Government of the United States a treaty of arbitration between the United
                    States of America and Austria as well as a conciliation treaty, and that it
                    fully approves of and consent to the wording of the pertaining drafts as
                    proposed by Your Excellency in your esteemed note of March 23rd,<note n="11"
                        xml:id="d813fn11">Not printed.</note> directed to this Legation.</p>
                <p>The special power to conclude and sign these treaties as well as their German
                    text is on the way and I shall not fail to notify Your Excellency as soon as
                    these papers reach me.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edgar Prochnik</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
